    <abstract id="aspace_398e04d46cd6926a5dabbca68e1be064">Diary of journey from Washington, DC, to Utah Territory in 1855 in which Burr describes the steamboat trip, life on the trail, the appearance of the land, Indians, and horse thieves. Letters written from Utah discussing details of the conflict between the Mormons and the U.S. government. Also included is an autograph album containing approximately 350 signatures.</abstract>
