  <dsc><c01 id="aspace_6383292e73f9cb262eec7dd72e35dc84" level="file"><did><unittitle>"Cornellian" photocopies of David E. Burr</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1902/1902" type="inclusive">1902</unitdate><container id="aspace_aacc6ef885e65d7a5fdaaa6d31fd8e41" label="Mixed Materials [31924064920923]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_22e013532c36f2c480c60eeff6abf9ec" parent="aspace_aacc6ef885e65d7a5fdaaa6d31fd8e41" type="folder">12</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_c1ae286da45975cceb02300ab3b9f09f" level="file"><did><unittitle>Letters between D.R. Eckels and P.K Dotson regarding Utah Territory</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1858-04/1858-04" type="inclusive">1858-04</unitdate><container id="aspace_957ef8b508432182d96fb220d657e069" label="Mixed Materials [31924064920923]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_1fd0ba06cf9e311c549dc38c54178c60" parent="aspace_957ef8b508432182d96fb220d657e069" type="folder">1</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_9c99ad73c52875f585964b09c535b003"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Two letters between D.R. Eckels, Chief Justice Supreme Court to P.K. Dotson, US Marshall. Dated April 21 and April 27, 1858.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_b1edd6b2848d06b94cc8e251fcf4ef50" level="file"><did><unittitle>Letter from David Burr describing a journey with the Army in the Utah Territory</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1858-04-09/1858-04-09" type="inclusive">1858-04-09</unitdate><container id="aspace_ce7efcd136e8118b0ee472c7e937a446" label="Mixed Materials [31924064920923]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_e53938329de1a6421e0b2f95ed9f5077" parent="aspace_ce7efcd136e8118b0ee472c7e937a446" type="folder">2</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_5b7c1c8246cbd88556876545c3da0512"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Xerox copy.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_12a2247e07a2bfd0fd6ef7b07bf91d5e" level="file"><did><unittitle>Letter to President James Buchanan</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1859-07-16/1859-07-16" type="inclusive">1859-07-16</unitdate><container id="aspace_04a5d5cdc11386f00c3271ece8da2773" label="Mixed Materials [31924064920923]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_3ea9f25272d213e163dd00db9d9644df" parent="aspace_04a5d5cdc11386f00c3271ece8da2773" type="folder">3</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_2c6dc723fd4a16196c17a3d22990a839"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Letter copied by David Burr, to President Buchanan from Justices Cradlebaugh and Sinclair.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_95d80f3cf6f89cefdb8e6ed171de832f" level="file"><did><unittitle>Report from Utah</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1858-08-21/1858-08-21" type="inclusive">1858-08-21</unitdate><container id="aspace_776393b6d457b4e226f18719ef36085b" label="Mixed Materials [31924064920923]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_5e36e1eacac2f656e108c5901617729f" parent="aspace_776393b6d457b4e226f18719ef36085b" type="folder">4</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_ef104244506801d240871e22a1d6846b"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Signed A.B.C. Commenting on the state of affairs in the Utah Territory and criticizing the editorial policy of the "Tribune." The author describes the turmoil within a group of Mormons and their church elders, as well as conflict between Mormons, the local Indigenous tribes, and the military.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_ccd0571e7c27bd94439ed10de028bd04" level="file"><did><unittitle>Letter from Burr to his father</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1859-11-27/1859-11-27" type="inclusive">1859-11-27</unitdate><container id="aspace_79a6d36dc6f5d19dce271f701e659121" label="Mixed Materials [31924064920923]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_bbabe3d0fd176e666c6d9023942a2f1d" parent="aspace_79a6d36dc6f5d19dce271f701e659121" type="folder">5</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_f731f18f260b36f7e11f09ddd0e73ed7"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Burr describes his journey home and the political reactions to the affairs in Utah.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_c8d00022b5865470bed91ce417d6fe05" level="file"><did><unittitle>Letter from Burr to his sister Louise</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1864-02-10/1864-02-10" type="inclusive">1864-02-10</unitdate><container id="aspace_3be8094c84478b7113cdaf9b4b429c53" label="Mixed Materials [31924064920923]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_e4e34be3bdfbe9c2c84e2c23404bbee8" parent="aspace_3be8094c84478b7113cdaf9b4b429c53" type="folder">5</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_322cd06235f25cf62e31a0dbeb99931b"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Burr describes his visits to Liverpool and Chester and his experiences on the journey to London.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_38f9ef8e684cee8ff01658358b745a76" level="file"><did><unittitle>Letter from Burr to his father</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1857-10-28/1857-10-28" type="inclusive">1857-10-28</unitdate><container id="aspace_3f8965edabf96b5a2621b417a211ca2d" label="Mixed Materials [31924064920923]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_a1b73f5443361a1fe576bb2d52beb921" parent="aspace_3f8965edabf96b5a2621b417a211ca2d" type="folder">6</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_7b605569c014b6779e5e5604254c38e0"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Burr describes recent events.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_7ae600eb423b09f17e0155c1d1bcd6d0" level="file"><did><unittitle>Letter from Burr to his mother</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1857-10-28/1857-10-28" type="inclusive">1857-10-28</unitdate><container id="aspace_10339123a77005909563081d7d577b36" label="Mixed Materials [31924064920923]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_17b0f3df6f34e2c4f488fdd38499779e" parent="aspace_10339123a77005909563081d7d577b36" type="folder">6</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_520f350648e4d93e53cdb587759116b7"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>In French.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_a2ca5cdd50fed692ffaaf4bd3161e219" level="file"><did><unittitle>Newspaper clipping, written by Burr</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1858-05-01/1858-05-01" type="inclusive">1858-05-01</unitdate><container id="aspace_54873dc00433cd3e886aabef9a02aeac" label="Mixed Materials [31924064920923]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_c0e1836572476193b1fc5af2d6e6008d" parent="aspace_54873dc00433cd3e886aabef9a02aeac" type="folder">7</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_3cc50adf3e874ded5076c07e57a342e4"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>"Late News from Utah, Interesting Intelligence Concerning the Army," written by Burr as a correspondent for the "New York Tribune."</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_743622e892c2dfd7d71d239a45cb2365" level="file"><did><unittitle>Essays and writings by Burr</unittitle><container id="aspace_5018c2fcc158824dd64cc4ca55f27c34" label="Mixed Materials [31924064920923]" type="box">1</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_0c098b255da8c319d008ef9ce0ff0851" level="file"><did><unittitle>"Wonders of Creation"</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1853-09-30/1853-09-30" type="inclusive">1853-09-30</unitdate><container id="aspace_c2b3fe7a8837487dbe69eb6fa6f240ca" label="Mixed Materials [31924064920923]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_693866e9965b6d7e7189750c6a26e80e" parent="aspace_c2b3fe7a8837487dbe69eb6fa6f240ca" type="folder">8</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_e0762717b7ed184297e71b5ca1b17fe7" level="file"><did><unittitle>"Industry"</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1853-10-07/1853-10-07" type="inclusive">1853-10-07</unitdate><container id="aspace_ebced18e39d4d958529cb453719d9bb5" label="Mixed Materials [31924064920923]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_9efd0eadfb3e5d406c947d25a2bfdeaf" parent="aspace_ebced18e39d4d958529cb453719d9bb5" type="folder">8</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_76c9492df6087743a8dca9fec4e4167c" level="file"><did><unittitle>"The Butterfly and Its Changes"</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1853-10-14/1853-10-14" type="inclusive">1853-10-14</unitdate><container id="aspace_3f3c1b176b5e3398a4b03e366643bed1" label="Mixed Materials [31924064920923]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_844b99046d324df66acee9a74ba1fa46" parent="aspace_3f3c1b176b5e3398a4b03e366643bed1" type="folder">8</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_b24ccb0a829ea7e8b29950bd99794763" level="file"><did><unittitle>"History"</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1853-10-27/1853-10-27" type="inclusive">1853-10-27</unitdate><container id="aspace_49e77b380b7233fe9f8a9b65714b8f92" label="Mixed Materials [31924064920923]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_64c2968d84e9246f2604e96c57fffaf9" parent="aspace_49e77b380b7233fe9f8a9b65714b8f92" type="folder">8</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_7dd27b1fb4b05a95b6d758623c8fb0d2" level="file"><did><unittitle>"The Sea"</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1853-11-11/1853-11-11" type="inclusive">1853-11-11</unitdate><container id="aspace_c587f09ba934cd5b6481766e2e46a18c" label="Mixed Materials [31924064920923]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_e44136666864d32f71d59bf943eeb3c7" parent="aspace_c587f09ba934cd5b6481766e2e46a18c" type="folder">8</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_8cc0b62dbce389b568a42120573befb4" level="file"><did><unittitle>"Excelsior" Vol 1, no. 1-3</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1853-11-25/1853-12-09" type="inclusive">1853-11-25-1853-12-09</unitdate><container id="aspace_591e9394cc7b42a177cd85f505f47200" label="Mixed Materials [31924064920923]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_ef342e5e86f1e81c821d86b438db5529" parent="aspace_591e9394cc7b42a177cd85f505f47200" type="folder">8</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_96a01f356687c0512e03f20b0a4b5e21"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>"Excelsior" was a newspaper written by David Burr and Eugene Burr.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_a954c576d219371d02254b341955b36e" level="file"><did><unittitle>Diary of David Burr</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1855/1855" type="inclusive">1855</unitdate><container id="aspace_d727fb9a87aedfc844351d1998ec9abc" label="Mixed Materials [31924065488441]" type="box">2</container><container id="aspace_85c36f0e36199f8a9368022a96b92ac4" parent="aspace_d727fb9a87aedfc844351d1998ec9abc" type="folder">1</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_75bde46bc06c82847ee080aa6a30bfbf"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Burr writes of his journey from Washington DC to the Utah Territory. Included are descriptions of a steamboat trip along the Mississippi, of life on the trail, of the flora, fauna, and topography of the regions passed through, and of incidents involving Indigenous people and horse thieves.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_b1e6fe5c99e8120c25177ce991385f63" level="file"><did><unittitle>Diary of David Burr</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1857-11-02/1857-11-16" type="inclusive">1857-11-02-1857-11-16</unitdate><container id="aspace_3539c2a86f747f6e35863b0bef99f09a" label="Mixed Materials [31924064920923]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_41b6c176c0f9aaef6f15efb4328e9e36" parent="aspace_3539c2a86f747f6e35863b0bef99f09a" type="folder">9</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_6dbbf3aa8988176f9d306289e52b356e"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>In these loose pages, Burr describes joining a military party and encountering Mormons. Back at camp, delegates sent by Brigham Young arrived to negotiate the return of prisoners and allowed Mrs. Mogo (wife of Charles Mogo) to be reunited with her husband and leave the Church. Burr further describes the military tactics of Brigham Young and some of his preachings. He reports that the Mormons had killed forty apostates who were trying to flee to California, and says he will write of Charles Mogo's escape from Salt Lake City. Burr also writes of the capture of Mormon prisoners.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_e7841bb8c0cfd8a92c7c813a3b05c516" level="file"><did><unittitle>Judicial Report:  The Collision between the Executive and Judicial Authorities of the Territory of Utah</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1858/1859" type="inclusive">1858-1859</unitdate><container id="aspace_85a8f9e1d68769e00a0d09259b74b01e" label="Mixed Materials [31924064920923]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_79c268dfb3ad8a217f1b874dead34f85" parent="aspace_85a8f9e1d68769e00a0d09259b74b01e" type="folder">11</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_ed3af4073de85e5710f3dbbaaeb8ac81"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>"A brief review of the attempts made by the U.S. Judges to administer law in Utah in 1858 - 1859, containing the correspondence between the judges and the President of the U.S. relative to the position of officers in the Territory, and other official documents heretofore unpublished." "From the private portfolio of the Clerk of the Supreme Court of Utah Territory"</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_2b3b0d08ecfdf369a0eaceebbe29cbcc" level="file"><did><unittitle>Photographs and sketches</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" datechar="creation" era="ce">Undated</unitdate><container id="aspace_93d4b2dc2bc9242cb1f922961b6b4d2d" label="Mixed Materials [31924064920923]" type="box">1</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_2ca123ae985f36ad0b978e49ea02ae11" level="file"><did><unittitle>The David H. Burr and David A. Burr Collection</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" datechar="creation" era="ce">Undated</unitdate><container id="aspace_2fe51b9b2022684bcba515cc7fac5ed2" label="Mixed Materials [31924064920923]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_7852ebdb5f2d28129caecffdb8b6d237" parent="aspace_2fe51b9b2022684bcba515cc7fac5ed2" type="folder">10</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_4b05c0b4f26324260cefb7bf5f2c151f