Scope and Contents</head><p>Album containing approximately 350 signatures collected by Mrs. David H. Burr and later members of her family, beginning in 1848 and continuing through 1969. Over three quarters of the autographs were collected in Washington, DC in the late 1840s and early 1850s, from the House of Representatives. Included are signatures of: Dolly Madison, Louisa Catherine Adams, Grace Greenwood, Fredrika Bremer, James Buchanan, Frederick D. Grant, William Jennings Bryan, William B. Preston, William Marcy, William R. King, A.P. Butler, Dan Sturgeon, Aylett Buckner, Charles Golden Atherton, A. Johnson, Jefferson Davis, Abraham Lincoln, Joseph Crane Hartzell, Millard Filmore, William Taft, Winston Churchill, among many others.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_519f22d9b83a0760f90342a3cf7422e9" level="file"><did><unittitle>Documents relating to autograph album</unittitle><container id="aspace_2c28a4e427bcb2e37854d86ab5497b38" label="Mixed Materials [31924065488441]" type="box">2</container><container id="aspace_4b25ebcdb74139169b0055344c0e5263" parent="aspace_2c28a4e427bcb2e37854d86ab5497b38" type="folder">2</container></did></c01></dsc>
